{"search_data": "Madhya PradeshMP Unmarried Women Pension Scheme \u2013 Mukhyamantri Avivahit Pension Yojana MP Mukhyamantri Avivahit Pension Yojana - Unmarried Women Pension Scheme approved by Madhya Pradesh cabinet, single elderly women b/w 50 to 79 to monthly pension of Rs. 300 & above 80 years to get Rs. 500 p.mMP Mukhyamantri Unmarried (Avivahit) Women Pension SchemeThe state cabinet meeting chaired by CM Shivraj Singh Chouhan cleared the proposal to start Unmarried Women Pension Scheme by the Social Welfare and Disability Welfare Department. Now, every women who is unmarried and belongs to MP and is above 50 years of age will receive monthly pension under Mukhyamantri Avivahit Pension Yojana.Single elderly women in the age group of 50 to 79 years will get monthly pension of Rs. 300 while those aged 80 years or above will get Rs. 500 per month. This scheme will ensure that all the elderly women who are still unmarried becomes financially independent.Cabinet committee has also given in-principle approval for separate rooms and toilets for women staff and complainants at around 676 police stations. This project for construction of separate rooms and toilets will cost around Rs 49.10 crore. In Madhya Pradesh, there are around 4.84 crore voters out of which 48% are female voters. These proposals are approved in order to woo the women voters in the state.MP Mukhyamantri Avivahit Pension YojanaThe other decisions are also taken in the state cabinet meeting on 24 September 2018. This includes approval to 405 posts for metro rail projects in Indore and Bhopal. Also the state govt. has approved the loan proposal of 500 million euro loan from European Investment Bank (EIB) for Bhopal Metro rail project. Now a feasibility report to start the metro rail project in Jabalpur and Gwalior would also be prepared.\u092e\u0941\u0916\u094d\u092f\u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 @ChouhanShivraj \u0915\u0940 \u0905\u0927\u094d\u092f\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0924\u093e \u092e\u0947\u090